Text.Value: Don't waste your time hoping. It's probably long dead.
I hope whatever killed them is still around. I will not have it soil Shar's name.
Indeed. We will avenge them if we can. And who knows? Perhaps other children of Shar are still to be found down here...

EditorData.NodeContext: Spoken to a fellow shar worshipper. They found the remains of some of their brethren in the underdark, long dead.

Text.Value: I'll keep an eye out. If it's a demon, I'll be able to spot it a mile off.

Text.Value: Let's get moving, then. Once we fill our packs with what we can carry, of course.
*You see nothing special - just torn and faded velvet tunics.*
Now, now. Take a breath, count to ten. This battle's been long-finished - no reason to fight it again.
You took the words right out of my mouth, soldier.
Look at those uniforms. They must have belonged to some kind of sect.
Don't turn on each other. If whatever managed to murder a group of Sharrans is still around, we had better watch our step.
Bah - let Shar exact her own revenge, if she's so inclined. Our concerns lie far elsewhere.
Yes, we should press forward. But let's not presume the past always remains buried.
Shar's name is no more our concern than a gnat's egg. Turn your attentions to something of actual import.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little solemn (She saw some of her comrade's bodies abandoned where they died - she may or may not be known as a Shar worshipper at this point).

Text.Value: If we must. Oh, but imagine what tales these bones might tell if they could.
Dark Justiciar uniforms... these were Shar worshippers - her most elite warriors. Curious.

Text.Value: Ominous. Let's not linger.
Let's not. But a word of warning: down here in the Underdark, few dangers ever truly die.
Unusually robust uniforms - warriors fallen in battle, perhaps.
If their killer's still around, it's not Shar's name I'm most interested in saving.
